01:04.000 --> 01:06.000
Claro que sí.

01:06.000 --> 01:12.000
Today, he's also the man who'll look you dead in the eye and tell you that the phenomena is real.

01:12.000 --> 01:20.000
The records about such unidentified celestial phenomena date back to antiquity.

01:20.000 --> 01:22.000
They're not new.

01:23.000 --> 01:27.000
In this unprecedented candid conversation, we cover it all.

01:27.000 --> 01:36.000
We get into the Chupa Chupa attacks in Kolares in the 70s, where UFOs in the Amazonian night sky allegedly fired mysterious beams

01:36.000 --> 01:42.000
that left villagers with burns, blood loss, and puncture wounds.

01:42.000 --> 01:45.000
A multi-month event affecting 200 people.

01:45.000 --> 01:51.000
So serious that the Air Force ran a real investigation on it called Operation Prata.

01:51.000 --> 02:04.000
We touch on Brazil's mass UFO radar incursions of 1986, an unforgettable night for the Brazilian military.

02:04.000 --> 02:09.000
And then there's Varginha, Brazil's very own modern-day Roswa.

02:09.000 --> 02:11.000
What the fuck are you playing now, brother?

02:13.000 --> 02:20.000
Rebello basically acknowledges that in 1996, in the small city of Varginha, something crashed.

02:20.000 --> 02:22.000
It was recovered.

02:22.000 --> 02:29.000
And a non-human creature, or multiple creatures, with slick, oily brown skin and big red eyes,

02:29.000 --> 02:32.000
was seen by multiple witnesses.

02:32.000 --> 02:35.000
And even treated by a neurosurgeon in a hospital.

02:35.000 --> 02:39.000
I know that sounds like a Spielberg movie you'd want to watch.

02:39.000 --> 02:42.000
It's actually a case that Spielberg is familiar with.

02:47.000 --> 02:49.000
Except this isn't Hollywood.

02:49.000 --> 02:56.000
This is the former Brazilian Minister of Defense sitting across from me, telling me it was real.

02:56.000 --> 03:03.000
In America, our equivalent would be a former Secretary of Defense, like a Jim Mattis or a Robert Gates,

03:03.000 --> 03:06.000
saying that Roswell was real.

03:06.000 --> 03:10.000
Saying candidly that, yeah, a saucer probably did crash in New Mexico.

03:10.000 --> 03:13.000
And beings probably did emerge from it.

03:13.000 --> 03:21.000
And in doing so, he gives validation and voice to all the witnesses, researchers, doctors, military personnel,

03:21.000 --> 03:27.000
and ordinary people who have been attacked, dismissed, and ridiculed over this subject for decades.

03:27.000 --> 03:32.000
And he provides shelter and safe haven to those who haven't come out yet.

03:32.000 --> 03:36.000
Believing that a phenomenon like this exists, of course.

03:36.000 --> 03:40.000
To Ribello, the real question isn't whether the phenomenon has occurred.

03:40.000 --> 03:47.000
It's where it came from, why it was here, and what it means for the future of science, society, defense,

03:47.000 --> 03:51.000
and where humanity stands in the universe.

03:51.000 --> 03:56.000
So with that, enjoy this historic conversation with Aldo Ribello,

03:56.000 --> 04:00.000
Brazil's former Minister of Defense, current presidential candidate,

04:00.000 --> 04:08.000
and the man who'll tell you that some of the strangest stories you've ever heard might also be the truest.

04:08.000 --> 04:11.000
Ignition sequence 5.

04:12.000 --> 04:14.000
How is this possible?

04:15.000 --> 04:17.000
Nothing too unusual about that.

04:19.000 --> 04:22.000
The existence cannot longer be denied.

